  "name": "Evolution Tree",
  "description": "The tree of life — 30 major transitions in evolution, from the first self-replicating molecules to the human mind. Each branch point represents a moment when life invented something new: a new body plan, a new way to eat, a new way to move, a new way to think. Tiered content for young children (Story) and older readers (Science).\n\nPUBLIC DOMAIN ILLUSTRATION REFERENCES: Ernst Haeckel (1834–1919), whose 'Kunstformen der Natur' (Art Forms in Nature, 1904) contains spectacular illustrations of radiolarians, jellyfish, and other organisms that celebrate the beauty of evolutionary diversity. Charles Darwin's own tree-of-life sketch from his notebook (1837).",
  "grammar_type": "custom",
  "creator_name": "PlayfulProcess",
